{"key":"post-9538770","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9538770</id>\n<content>The toggle valve you have is superior to the nozzle and weight combination.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You leave the toggle up for the first ten minutes or so to allow steam to escape, and then you flip it down to build pressure.&amp;nbsp; Use your stove control to adjust pressure to between 14 psi and 18 psi.&amp;nbsp; At the end of the cycle, turn your stove off.&amp;nbsp; Don't lift the toggle to vent steam or you'll dry out the substrate and/or break the jars.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9538886</next>\n<prev>9537973</prev>\n<first>9537866</first>\n<last>9538918</last>\n<when>1231024638</when>\n<utime>01/04/09 01:17 AM</utime>\n</post>"}